        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 12:21PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1221 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Sawyer to near Sumner. Movement was
northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and dime to penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Ord...                            Grant...
Corinne...                        Fallon...
Sobol...                          Swink...
Goodland...                       Sawyer...
Frogville...                      Messer...
Hugo Lake State Park...           Apple...
Raymond Gary State Park...        Hugo...
Huskey...                         Oleta...
Fort Towson...                    Arthur City...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
